      <title type="html">My first post!</title>
      
      <link href="/2018/03/08/my-first-post/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="My first post!" />
      <published>2018-03-08T18:21:00+00:00</published>
      <updated>2018-03-08T18:21:00+00:00</updated>
      <id>/2018/03/08/my-first-post</id>
      <content type="html" xml:base="/2018/03/08/my-first-post/">&lt;p&gt;This is my first post using &lt;a href=&quot;https://jekyllrb.com/&quot;&gt;Jekyll&lt;/a&gt;. Setting it up is easy. Next step will be to look into &lt;strong&gt;themes&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To install Jekyll locally into an existing directory:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;language-shell highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo gem install -n /usr/local/bin jekyll bundler
jekyll new . --force
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To view you site locally:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;language-shell highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;bundle &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;exec &lt;/span&gt;jekyll serve
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and go to http://127.0.0.1:4000/&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To push it to GitHub:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;language-shell highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git add .; git commit -m &lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;'new posts'&lt;/span&gt;
git push
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</content>

      
      
      
      
      

      
